Subject: Don't depend on libcgmanager-dev
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

As of lxcfs 0.11, libcgmanager isn't used anymore, instead lxcfs talks
to cgmanager using glib-dbus.

Signed-off-by: St√©phane Graber <stgraber@ubuntu.com>
---
 configure.ac | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/configure.ac b/configure.ac
index 0082715..cac68aa 100644
--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -26,7 +26,6 @@ AC_CHECK_LIB(pthread, main)
 PKG_CHECK_MODULES([GLIB], [glib-2.0])
 PKG_CHECK_MODULES([GLIBDBUS], [dbus-glib-1])
 PKG_CHECK_MODULES(GIO, gio-2.0)
-PKG_CHECK_MODULES([CGMANAGER], [libcgmanager >= 0.0.0])
 PKG_CHECK_MODULES(FUSE, fuse)
 
 AC_PATH_PROG(HELP2MAN, help2man, false // No help2man //)
